caption: Excellent Peruvian chicken. Reasonable prices. Fast service.

I like this place! They serve good meals, their menu is decent, The cook in that place is very experienced, I enjoy a lot tasting all their dishes. The dishes are consistently of high class, the attitude towards the visitors  is helpful. I frequently visit this place and I was never unhappy. I recommend it to all.

Delicious chicken
The best Peruvian takeaway that isn't overly priced in the area. Good food, very fast, and for a great price.
One of my go-to places in downtown Bethesda. The 1/2 chicken (dark meat) with 2 sides is perfect, the chicken is delicious. A great option for lunch and dinner!

BEWARE! DO NOT order online with a credit card and do not expect to get curbside orders - when you arrive the owner will insist that he never got the order and stick you with the charge. I showed him the credit card notification and he did not believe. If you must, cash only or not at all!
Loved the food! Spiced right, priced right. Good place for a quick meal or family meal. Eat in or take out.

Great place for quick cheap eats. I love for their beans, rice, and sweet plantains.  I don’t know what they do to the chicken, but it is amazing. A great place to feed a crowd with solid comfort food.
Great quick eats. Central American rotisserie  chicken and yummy sides -- plantain, yuka, beans and rice, and divine mashed potatoes.  Good price.
Very tasty! Great flavor every meal.

Cozy, relatively inexpensive hole in the wall! We got the quarter white meat with plantains and rice/black beans as sides. The plantains were my favorite being the right amount of sweet and crispy. Definitely a spot to check out
Great food at a great price.
Consistently good chicken, and the yucca is always hot and fresh.
For a menu and they say they don’t have one. Plus they were very rude so I’m thinking why waste my time with a restaurant that has bad attitude.

I placed an order online and they messed it up three times. The first time I called to get the right order, I told the lady on the phone I wanted a refund and she refused because “the manager wasn’t there”. My coworker went to pick up my food the third time and instead of being apologetic for making me come down three times, the lady from the phone told my co worker she was expecting me because she had somethings to say to me about respect. my coworker felt very uncomfortable due to her attitude and demeanor when she said this. They claimed I was being disrespectful on the phone towards them because they’re Hispanic. I’m Hispanic. I wasn’t talking down to anyone. I just want the right order I paid for. I called back to speak to a manager about the workers comment, “I was hoping she would come down to get her food so I could tell her a few things” (Spanish) but instead got to speak to Clemente who said he was the manager. But at first they couldn’t refund me because there was no manager? It doesn’t make sense. These people are liars. the whole situation was not okay and what did the lady need to tell me ? or if they actually need me to go down? At this time it was male on the phone who claimed to be the manager. They call him “el Chaparro”. And later on said his name is Clemente. And the lady on the phone was “Lucia”.

Great!

I went in and had to wait at least 5mins just to place my order, now that may not seem like a long time, but when you're on a 30min lunch break it is! Once my order was FINALLY taken and they took my money I see the cook start to make the rice. Which I think they should've given me the option if I wanted to wait. Long story short I got a refund and had to find something else to eat with 20mins ro spare smh. I feel like it shouldn't have taken that long for a side order! They were very unapologetic
Good place to get some awesome chicken
Great food for little money.  You can't go wrong with the half chicken with two sides.

A true gem - we order food here about once per week and are never disappointed! The chicken is always juicy and full of flavor. The sides are phenomenal. And the price just can not be beat! Highly recommend to any and every one.
Fast. Great price. Sizeable portions, and best of all...it's delicious!

THE WORST PLACE!!!! They messed up my order so many times and not only that, I found hair in my food twice! My chicken didn't seem to be fresh! When I told the staff about my issues they were rude! When I asked to speak with management, they didn't let me! The employees are extremely dishonest and unprofessional! The owner is also careless and unprofessional! I was shocked by my experience! My wife and I share the 1/2 chicken beans and rice with fries weekly. Best buy in the area, extra sauce is a must.

Yummy!

This is a great hole in the wall type place.  Pretty decent prices despite being raised a little over the past few years.  I've really only stuck with one thing on the menu and thats the 1/4 White Chicken with mac n cheese on the side.  Can't beat that!  This is definitely a good lunch place for the size portion you get since you won't walk away stuffed but definitely not feeling like you need more.

I am a regular customer and live within walking distance. As I walked up 25 minutes before close, the last staff locked the doors. If I was the owner, I'd be furious. I usually go to chicken on the run 1-2 times a week, I may not return unless something is done to deal with the rude staff that doesn't respect their owners or their customers

The food is ok (but does not compare with the gold standard "Pollo Rico" in Wheaton). But, the chicken is tiny (1/4 chicken will leave a normal person - me - still hungry) and the prices are very high - $8.50 (dark) for a small lunch. More for white meat. The value is not there at all. I can't recommend this place and this is the last time I'll go there.

The 1/4 dark chicken, fries and bean and rice with a drink was the PERFECT meal!  I mixed the green and tan sauce they gave me and dipped my chicken in it and WOW!  Then I added ketchup to it for my fries.  It was awesome.  I'm 100% coming back.
